
•	JWT (JSON Web token): HPS (Header, Payload, Signature)
•	How to secure JWT: 
  1.	SSL
  2.	Token Expiry
  3.	Sign JWTs with Strong Secret or RSA Key

----------
0Auth: OAuth (specifically OAuth 2.0) is an authorization framework, not authentication. 
It allows applications to access resources on behalf of a user without exposing the user’s credentials.

o	Offloads complex authentication logic (passwords, MFA, login flows).
o	Single Sign-On (SSO) support.
o	Built-in token issuance, validation, and revocation.



